Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Dice @sweet potatoes{1} into 1⁄2-inch pieces. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Peel and mince or grate @garlic{2%cloves}.

Toss sweet potato on one side of a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{drizzle}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{20-22%minutes} (you'll add more to the sheet after 11 minutes).

While sweet potato roasts, using a #rolling pin{} or #heavy-bottomed pan{}, crush @bold & savory steak spice{1%tablespoon} peppercorns inside packet of Steak Spice.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with 1 1/2 tsp Steak Spice (all for 4 servings), a big pinch of salt, and pepper.

> Swap in chicken or beef for pork. Cook chicken until browned and cooked through, 6-8 minutes per side, or cook beef to desired doneness, 4-7 minutes per side.

Heat a drizzle of cooking oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium heat. Add cutlets and sear, turning occasionally, until browned all over, ~{4-8%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Once sweet potato has roasted 11 minutes, remove baking sheet from oven. Carefully toss sweet potato; add cutlets to empty side of baking sheet.

Return to top rack until pork is cooked through and sweet potato is browned and tender, ~{9-11%minutes}. Transfer cutlets to a #cutting board{} to rest for at least ~{5%minutes}.

Skip this step for chicken or beef!

Meanwhile, melt 1 TBSP @butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) in a #medium pot{} over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites and half the garlic (you'll use the rest in the next step); cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Add @Israeli couscous{5%ounce} and stir to coat. Stir in 1 1/2 cups water (2 1/4 cups for 4 servings), @chicken stock concentrate{1}, and a big pinch of salt. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until couscous is tender, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Drain any excess liquid if necessary. Season with salt and pepper if desired. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While couscous cooks, heat a drizzle of cooking oil{} in pan used for pork over medium heat. Add remaining garlic and cook, stirring often, until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Add 1/4 cup water (1/3 cup for 4 servings), @mushroom stock concentrate{1}, and @cream cheese{2%tablespoons}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until cream cheese melts and sauce has thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Remove from heat and stir in 1 TBSP butter (2 TBSP for 4). Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

> Use pan used for chicken or beef here.

Stir roasted sweet potato into pot with couscous. Thinly slice cutlets crosswise.

Divide couscous and cutlets between plates. Spoon pan sauce over cutlets. Garnish with scallion greens and serve.

> Thinly slice chicken or beef against the grain.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.